cs.SC, cs.NA, cs.SY, cs.DS, cs.CG

Reasoning: 
- cs.SC (Symbolic Computation) is the most likely category as the paper deals with symbolic-numeric algorithms for the certification of singular isolated points.
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper involves certified numerical computations and iterative schemes with quadratic convergence.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with polynomial systems and their analysis.
- cs.DS (Dynamical Systems) is relevant as the paper discusses the multiplicity structure of singular points and their deflation.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is relevant as the paper applies the method to the analysis of real branches of an implicit curve.
